    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a mechanically sound driver\u2019s car powered by the iconic S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS high-pressure oil pump upgrades. The power is delivered through a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox to a limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal torque distribution. Significant preventative maintenance has been performed, including a comprehensive rear subframe reinforcement and rod bearing inspection, addressing the primary structural concerns of this chassis. The suspension geometry remains tight with upgraded poly-bushings, and the naturally aspirated induction note is crisp through the entire 8,000 RPM range. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina, the drivetrain synchronization and throttle response are dialed in for high-performance use.",
